BREAST-COMPOSITION: Heterogeneously dense glandular breast parenchyma (ACR D)
FINDINGS: A 1.2 cm complex mass with spiculated margins seen in the upper-outer quadrant of the left breast, concerning for a suspicious abnormality (BIRADS 4B). Multiple microcalcifications are noted within and around the mass. No skin or nipple changes observed. Enlarged axillary lymph nodes are present but appear benign.
